  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Financial autonomy and empowerment of women in the Cotagaita and Vitichi municipalities, Bolivia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACLO Potosi, with funding from CAFOD and Jersey Overseas Aid will support 200 rural women from 24 communities in the Cotagaita and Vitichi, municipalities of the Potos&#xED; department &#x2013; an area severely affected by climate change &#x2013; to engage in sustainable agricultural practices that will help to increase their earning potential and guarantee food security. Recognising that women&#x2019;s economic gains will only be sustained when coupled with their political and social autonomy, the project will also strengthen women&#x2019;s decision-making and leadership skills so they can engage with, influence and comply with local public bodies. The project will provide seeds, equipment and training for rural women to engage in agricultural-based income-generation activities, as well as facilitate workshops for women to learn how to access markets and protect their rights. This project will be implemented by CAFOD&#x2019;s long-term partner in Bolivia, Fundaci&#xF3;n Acci&#xF3;n Cultural Loyola (ACLO) who have been supporting communities in the region for over forty years.</narrative>
  </description>
